# Comprehensive .gitignore for Both Sides AI Debate App
# Frontend (Next.js) + Backend (NestJS) + Documentation

# ===== DEPENDENCIES =====
**/node_modules/
**/.pnp
**/.pnp.*
**/.yarn/*
!**/.yarn/patches
!**/.yarn/plugins
!**/.yarn/releases
!**/.yarn/versions
**/yarn-error.log
**/npm-debug.log*
**/yarn-debug.log*
**/.pnpm-debug.log*

# ===== BUILD OUTPUTS =====
# Next.js
**/.next/
**/out/
**/build/
**/dist/

# NestJS
**/backend/dist/
**/backend/build/

# TypeScript
**/*.tsbuildinfo
**/next-env.d.ts

# ===== TESTING =====
**/coverage/
**/.nyc_output/
**/test-results/
**/playwright-report/

# ===== ENVIRONMENT & CONFIG =====
**/.env*
!**/.env.example
**/.vercel
**/.railway

# ===== DATABASE =====
**/*.db
**/*.sqlite
**/*.sqlite3
**/prisma/migrations/migration_lock.toml

# ===== LOGS =====
**/logs/
**/*.log
**/lerna-debug.log*

# ===== CACHING =====
**/.cache/
**/.parcel-cache/
**/.eslintcache
**/.npm

# ===== OS & SYSTEM FILES =====
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
ehthumbs.db
Thumbs.db
**/*.swp
**/*.swo
**/*~

# ===== IDEs & EDITORS =====
.vscode/settings.json.user
.vscode/launch.json.user
.idea/
*.sublime-workspace
*.sublime-project

# ===== TEMPORARY FILES =====
**/.tmp/
**/.temp/
**/tmp/
**/temp/

# ===== PACKAGE OUTPUTS =====
**/*.tgz
**/.yarn-integrity

# ===== DOCUMENTATION BUILD =====
**/docs/.vitepress/cache
**/docs/.vitepress/dist

# ===== SECURITY & SENSITIVE =====
**/*.pem
**/*.key
**/*.cert
**/*.p12
**/*.pfx

# ===== AI & ML =====
**/models/
**/embeddings/
**/*.pkl
**/*.h5

# ===== PROJECT SPECIFIC =====
# Keep important documentation files
!README.md
!**/README.md
!*.md
!**/*.md

# But ignore generated docs
**/api-docs/
**/coverage-docs/

# Backend specific ignores
**/backend/uploads/
**/backend/storage/
